# YAML Utilization Across Application Lifecycle

The YAML files in this project serve as the "blueprints" for different stages of your application's life—from code development and testing to production deployment and monitoring.

## 1. Development & Continuous Integration (CI)
These files automate the process of checking your code and preparing it for deployment.

| File Path | Tool | Role |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| [deploy.yml](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/SEO%20optimization/.github/workflows/deploy.yml) | **GitHub Actions** | Triggered on every push to `main`. It performs linting (code quality check), runs tests, and builds the Docker image to be pushed to Docker Hub. |
| [jenkins-setup.yaml](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/SEO%20optimization/k8s/jenkins-setup.yaml) | **Jenkins / K8s** | Sets up the Jenkins build server itself within a Kubernetes cluster. It configures permissions, networking, and Docker integration so Jenkins can manage your build pipelines. |

## 2. Infrastructure & Orchestration (CD)
These files define how the application should be "bottled" and run in a production environment like Kubernetes.

| File Path | Tool | Role |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| [deployment.yaml](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/SEO%20optimization/k8s/deployment.yaml) | **Kubernetes** | The main configuration for running your app. It specifies how many "replicas" (instances) to run, resource limits (CPU/Memory), environment variables, and health check endpoints. |
| [service.yaml](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/SEO%20optimization/k8s/service.yaml) | **Kubernetes** | Handles networking. It creates a `LoadBalancer` that allows users to access your application (on port 80) by routing traffic to the internal app port (8501). |

## 3. Alternative Cloud Deployment (PaaS)
This file is used for a simpler, "hands-off" deployment method.

| File Path | Tool | Role |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| [render.yaml](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/SEO%20optimization/render.yaml) | **Render.com** | A "Blueprint" for Render. It allows you to deploy the entire stack as a web service directly from this repository without manually configuring a Kubernetes cluster. |

---

### Summary of the "Flow"
1. **GitHub Actions** ([deploy.yml](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/SEO%20optimization/.github/workflows/deploy.yml)) lints and builds your image.
2. **Kubernetes** ([deployment.yaml](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/SEO%20optimization/k8s/deployment.yaml) & [service.yaml](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/SEO%20optimization/k8s/service.yaml)) ensures your app is running smoothly and is reachable by users.
3. **Jenkins** ([jenkins-setup.yaml](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/SEO%20optimization/k8s/jenkins-setup.yaml)) provides an internal build environment if you choose to use it instead of GitHub Actions.
4. **Render** ([render.yaml](file:///c:/Users/HP/Desktop/SEO%20optimization/render.yaml)) provides an alternative, simpler way to host your app in the cloud.
